<p><strong>Saving Throws</strong> Dex +5, Con +6, Int +5, Wis +4</p>

<p><strong>Skills</strong> Perception +7</p>

<p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision 120 ft.</p>

<p><strong>Languages</strong> Sahuagin</p>

<p><strong>Challenge</strong> 5 (1,800 XP)</p>

<p><strong><em>Blood Frenzy.</em></strong> The sahuagin has advantage on melee attack rolls against any creature that doesnâ€™t have all its hit points.</p>

<p><strong><em>Limited Amphibiousness.</em></strong> The sahuagin can breathe air and water, but it needs to be submerged at least once every 4 hours to avoid suffocating.</p>

<p><strong><em>Shark Telepathy.</em></strong> The sahuagin can magically command any shark within 120 feet of it, using a limited telepathy.</p>

<p><strong>Actions</strong></p>

<p><strong><em>Multiattack.</em></strong> The sahuagin makes three attacks: one with his bite and two with his claws or trident.</p>

<p><strong><em>Bite.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 9 (2d4 + 4) piercing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Claws.</em></strong> Melee Weapon Attack: +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 11 (2d6 + 4) slashing damage.</p>

<p><strong><em>Trident.</em></strong> Melee or Ranged Weapon Attack: +7 to hit, reach 5 ft. or range 20/60 ft., one target. Hit: 11 (2d6 + 4) piercing damage, or 13 (2d8 + 4) piercing damage if used with two hands to make a melee attack.</p>

